---

<PageShell
  title="Ireland Investor Visa 2026: Immigrant Investor Programme (IIP) Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Ireland's Immigrant Investor Programme (IIP). Investment options from €500,000, private health insurance required, path to citizenship, and English-speaking EU access."
  headline="Ireland Investor Visa: Immigrant Investor Programme Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about Ireland's IIP—investment options, insurance requirements, processing times, and the path to Irish citizenship in an English-speaking EU country."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Investor Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/visas/investor-visa-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Irish Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      English-Speaking EU Country
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Programme Suspension Warning -->
  <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-300 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
      </svg>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-red-900 text-lg mb-2">Programme Currently Suspended</h3>
        <p class="text-red-800 mb-2">
          As of February 2024, Ireland's Immigrant Investor Programme (IIP) is <strong>suspended</strong> and not accepting new applications. The Irish government has not announced a reopening date.
        </p>
        <p class="text-red-700 text-sm">
          This guide provides complete programme details for reference and for those planning ahead if the programme reopens. We recommend monitoring official Irish government announcements and considering alternative options like Portugal's Golden Visa in the meantime.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Ireland's Immigrant Investor Programme (IIP) has been one of Europe's most attractive investor visa options for high net worth individuals seeking EU residency. As an English-speaking country with a strong economy, favorable tax treaties, and gateway access to the European Union (especially post-Brexit), Ireland offers unique advantages for international investors and their families.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The programme allowed non-EEA nationals to secure Irish residency by making qualifying investments in the Irish economy. Unlike many investor programmes, the IIP had no minimum physical residency requirement—you only needed to visit Ireland once per year to maintain your status.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Ireland Immigrant Investor Programme</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Status:</strong> Currently SUSPENDED (February 2024)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Investment minimum:</strong> €500,000 (endowment) to €2,000,000 (REIT)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Net worth requirement:</strong> €2,000,000 minimum</li>
        <li>• <strong>Health insurance:</strong> Private insurance REQUIRED</li>
        <li>• <strong>Residence requirement:</strong> 1 day per year (when active)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Family included:</strong> Spouse and children under 24</li>
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> 2 years initial, then 3 years, then 5 years</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to citizenship:</strong> 5 years (naturalization)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Processing time:</strong> 4-6 months (when active)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Ireland?</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Ireland stands out among EU investor visa destinations for several reasons:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Unique Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Only English-speaking EU country (post-Brexit)</li>
          <li>• Common law legal system (similar to US, UK)</li>
          <li>• No minimum stay requirement</li>
          <li>• Strong education system</li>
          <li>• EU passport access through citizenship</li>
          <li>• Favorable corporate tax environment</li>
          <li>• Gateway to EU market (500M+ consumers)</li>
          <li>• No language requirement for residency</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Key Cities for Investors</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• <strong>Dublin:</strong> Capital, tech hub, headquarters for Google, Meta, Microsoft</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cork:</strong> Second city, pharma and tech center</li>
          <li>• <strong>Galway:</strong> West coast, medical device industry</li>
          <li>• <strong>Limerick:</strong> Growing tech scene, lower cost</li>
          <li>• World-class golf, countryside, and coastline</li>
          <li>• Short flights to UK and mainland Europe</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Alternative: Start-up Entrepreneur Programme (STEP)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For entrepreneurs with innovative business ideas but lower capital, Ireland also offers (when active) the Start-up Entrepreneur Programme (STEP) with a minimum investment of €50,000 in an Irish start-up company. STEP requires you to be actively involved in the business, unlike the passive investment options in the IIP.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Post-Brexit context:</strong> Since the UK left the EU, Ireland has become the only English-speaking country in the EU and remains in the Common Travel Area with the UK. This unique positioning makes Irish residency particularly valuable for those wanting EU access while maintaining strong ties to the Anglophone world.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ireland IIP is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ You have €2M+ net worth and €500K-2M to invest</li>
          <li>✓ You value English-speaking business environment</li>
          <li>✓ You want EU access without relocating full-time</li>
          <li>✓ Education quality matters for your children</li>
          <li>✓ You're comfortable with common law system</li>
          <li>✓ You want a path to EU citizenship</li>
          <li>✓ You can afford €150-500/month for insurance</li>
          <li>✓ You can wait for programme to reopen</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You need residency immediately (programme suspended)</li>
          <li>• You have less than €2M net worth</li>
          <li>• You prefer warmer climate (try Portugal, Spain)</li>
          <li>• You want lower investment thresholds (try Portugal)</li>
          <li>• You want to physically reside full-time in EU</li>
          <li>• You prefer real estate investment (Portugal better)</li>
          <li>• You want faster citizenship (Portugal at 5 years)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>While suspended:</strong> Consider Portugal's Golden Visa (from €500,000 fund investment), Malta's Permanent Residence Programme, or Spain's Golden Visa as alternatives. Portugal offers similar fund investment options with established track record.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Investment Requirements -->
  <section id="investment-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Investment Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      When active, Ireland's IIP offered four investment options. All require proof of minimum €2 million net worth from legally acquired sources, with the investment funds themselves needing independent verification of origin.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={investmentColumns} rows={investmentRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Investment Options Explained</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Enterprise Investment (€1,000,000)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Invest directly in a new or existing Irish business. The enterprise must be headquartered in Ireland and create or maintain employment. Can be a single investment or spread across multiple enterprises. Investment must remain for at least 3 years. Most common choice for those wanting active involvement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Investment Fund (€1,000,000)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Invest in an approved Irish investment fund that invests in Irish businesses. The fund must be approved by the Irish Immigration Service and regulated by the Central Bank of Ireland. Lower risk than direct enterprise investment as funds are professionally managed and diversified. Most popular option for passive investors.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Real Estate Investment Trust (€2,000,000)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Invest in any Irish REIT or combination of REITs listed on the Main Securities Market of the Irish Stock Exchange. Must maintain investment for at least 3 years. Higher minimum than other options but offers real estate exposure with liquidity. Less common due to higher threshold.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Endowment/Donation (€500,000)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Non-refundable donation to a project of public benefit in arts, sports, health, culture, or education. Lowest threshold but no return on investment. Can qualify for group donation of €400,000 if 5+ investors donate to the same project. Popular for those prioritizing entry over returns.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Financial Requirements</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Net Worth Requirement (€2M)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Total assets minus liabilities</li>
          <li>• Can include property, investments, business equity</li>
          <li>• Must be legally acquired</li>
          <li>• Verified by independent accountant</li>
          <li>• Excludes the investment amount itself</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Source of Funds Documentation</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Audited business accounts</li>
          <li>• Sale of property documentation</li>
          <li>• Investment portfolio statements</li>
          <li>• Inheritance documentation</li>
          <li>• Gift documentation (if applicable)</li>
          <li>• Tax returns and compliance proof</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Due diligence is rigorous:</strong> Ireland conducts thorough background checks on all applicants. Source of funds must be clearly documented and legally obtained. Applications with unclear wealth origins or connections to high-risk jurisdictions face additional scrutiny or rejection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Private Health Insurance is Required</h3>
      <p class="text-green-800">
        IIP applicants and their dependents must have private health insurance covering them in Ireland. This is a mandatory condition of the programme. You cannot rely solely on the public HSE (Health Service Executive) system initially—private insurance is required from day one.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Ireland has a two-tier healthcare system: the public HSE system available to ordinary residents, and a robust private healthcare sector. As an investor visa holder, you'll initially rely on private insurance, though you may gain access to certain HSE services after establishing ordinary residency.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Public vs. Private Healthcare in Ireland</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Insurance Requirements for IIP</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Your health insurance must meet the following criteria:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li>Cover inpatient and outpatient treatment in Ireland</li>
      <li>Include emergency and routine medical care</li>
      <li>Cover all family members included in the application</li>
      <li>Be valid from the date of approval</li>
      <li>No annual or lifetime caps that would leave you underinsured</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Choose International Insurance If:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ You travel frequently between countries</li>
          <li>✓ You want coverage outside Ireland</li>
          <li>✓ You prefer premium service levels</li>
          <li>✓ You want a single provider across regions</li>
          <li>✓ You value English-speaking customer service</li>
          <li>✓ You may seek treatment in multiple countries</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Choose Irish Private Insurance If:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>✓ You'll primarily be based in Ireland</li>
          <li>✓ You want access to all Irish private hospitals</li>
          <li>✓ You prefer local provider relationships</li>
          <li>✓ You want potentially lower premiums</li>
          <li>✓ You're comfortable with Irish system</li>
          <li>✓ You don't need global coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Tax relief on insurance:</strong> Ireland offers tax relief on private health insurance premiums at the standard rate (20%). The relief is typically applied at source by the insurer, effectively reducing your premium cost.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox
    variant="highlight"
    title="Need insurance for your Ireland investor visa?"
    description="Compare international and Irish private health insurance options for high net worth individuals and families."
    buttonText="Compare Investor Insurance"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For IIP investors, you have two main options: international health insurance from global providers (ideal if you travel frequently) or Irish private health insurance (best if you'll spend significant time in Ireland). Both satisfy visa requirements.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">High Net Worth Individual, Frequent Traveler</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cigna Global or Bupa Global offers comprehensive worldwide coverage with premium service levels. Direct billing at top hospitals globally, 24/7 multilingual support, and seamless coverage across countries. Higher cost but matches the lifestyle of mobile investors.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Family Relocating to Ireland Full-Time</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">VHI Healthcare or Laya Healthcare provides excellent Irish coverage with established networks across Dublin, Cork, and Galway. Strong pediatric and maternity coverage, familiar with Irish system. Supplement with travel insurance for international trips.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Investor Maintaining Multiple Residences</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Allianz Care offers flexible international plans that cover Ireland plus other countries where you spend time. Good balance of comprehensive coverage and cost. Can customize regional coverage based on your travel patterns.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Cost-Conscious Applicant Meeting Requirements</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Irish Life Health offers solid coverage at competitive rates. Meets visa requirements while keeping costs manageable. Good for those who need compliant coverage but don't need premium global service.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
