    <p class="mb-4">
      However, with the programme currently suspended, prospective investors must either wait for a potential reopening or consider alternatives. Portugal's Golden Visa offers similar fund investment options with an established track record. Malta's programmes provide alternative EU access. The UK's investor visa route has also evolved post-Brexit.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      For those committed to Ireland specifically, the Start-up Entrepreneur Programme (STEP) may offer an alternative path with lower capital requirements (€50,000) if you have an innovative business idea—though it requires active business involvement rather than passive investment.
